Class Keyword

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualitestgroup.kdt.framework.Keyword
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Baseline.MoveToBaseline, Baseline.MoveToHistory, Baseline.SaveExecutionData, Browser.Close, Browser.GetElement, Browser.GetPageTitle, Browser.Launch, Browser.NavigateTo, Browser.RefreshBrowser, Browser.VerifyElementEnabledStatus, Browser.VerifyElementSelectedStatus, Browser.VerifyElementText, Browser.VerifyElementVisibleStatus, Browser.VerifyMultipleElement, Browser.VerifyMultipleElementEnabledStatus, Browser.VerifyMultipleElementText, Browser.VerifyTextBoxCharLimit, Common.AddDaysToCurrentDateExcludeWeekends, Common.Concatenate, Common.GetCurrentDateTime, Common.GoTo, Common.LoadConfigurationData, Common.MoveDirectory, Common.Pause, Common.Print, Common.RepeatKeyword, Common.RetrieveGlobal, Common.RetrieveLocal, Common.Screenshot, Common.StoreGlobal, Common.StoreLocal, Common.Validate, Common.Wait, Database.Connect, Database.ConnectionKeyword, Database.ExecuteQuery, MobileApplication.Launch

    public abstract class Keyword
extends Object
    Abstract class for keywords. Implementing classes must provide override the exec function. The init and cleanup methods can be overridden to provide more functionality.
    Author:
    lenovo

      • run

        public static final boolean run(String application,
                                String keyword,
                                String... args)
                         throws com.qualitestgroup.kdt.framework.exceptions.KDTException
        Runs a keyword.
        Parameters:
        application - The Application (KeywordGroup) containing the keyword.
        keyword - The name of the keyword.
        args - Arguments for the keyword. Alternates between Name and Value (Name1, Value1, Name2, Value2, ...)
        Throws:
        com.qualitestgroup.kdt.framework.exceptions.KDTException - If the keyword can't be found, the number of args is odd, or the keyword throws an error.
